steps.text:
`OutlinedInput` expects custom `inputComponent`s to consume an `inputRef` prop. `TextareaAutosize` uses the normal React `ref`, so `inputRef` leaks through to its `<textarea>` and React warns.

Prefer the built-in multiline path:

```jsx
<OutlinedInput
  multiline
  rowsMin={3}
  rowsMax={8}
/>
```

MUI will use `TextareaAutosize` internally.

If you must supply it through `inputComponent`, adapt the ref interface:

```jsx
const AutosizeInput = React.forwardRef(function AutosizeInput(props, ref) {
  const { inputRef, ...other } = props;

  return <TextareaAutosize {...other} ref={inputRef || ref} />;
});

<OutlinedInput inputComponent={AutosizeInput} />
```

The adapter is necessary because `inputRef` is a Material-UI custom-input convention, not a valid DOM `<textarea>` attribute.
